result.adr_address: G/F, 184A Temple St, Jordan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: G/F, 184A Temple St, Jordan, Hong Kong
result.name: Tong Tai Sea Food Restaurant

reviews.text:
Always a Great Treat dining at Tong Tai. Get some cold beer from the Kiosk on the other side of the corner, and tuck in to Spicy Buffalo Wings , Big Shrimp in Chilli and Garlic sauce, Sweet and Sour Pork and special fried Rice.
I generally order too much , then eat too much , but leave feeling like a well stuffed Emperor.
Next time I'm in Hong Kong I'll be back for more!
Nice cheap beer, which is good and cheap, means it's good. And the food is also nice. They have deep fried baby pigeon but i was too lazy to try.
Overrated and overpriced. Tourist trap.
Nice staff, good food. Also for people, who don’t eat sea food. Bit pricey, but not too much. Nice to watch at other people at the market walking by...

Can enjoy both delicious food and the vibrations of temple street night market.
"Garlic chilli prawns" is one of the best dish. Though it is a bit much spicy, cold beer will match the strong spice. Beers are quite inexpensive compared to usual restaurants.

result.adr_address: 184 Temple St, Jordan, Hong Kong
result.name: Tang Tai Street Restaurant

reviews.text:
It is very expensive, and most fried foods are not fresh, just to deceive those who do not understand Chinese food. Going to Kowloon City, Sham Shui Po and Shek Kip Mei will be cheaper and fresher.
Yau Ma Tei takes the MTR Kwun Tong Line to Lok Fu. Leave the subway station, go straight, look at the Hengtou Road, walk a few steps to the left, take a taxi about 30 yuan to Kowloon City.

Order the oyster omelette! So generous with the oyster and fresh and it’s the highlight and start of our dinner here! I can eat that all day long. And even my husband who’s not a huge fan of oyster loved it- it’s says a lot about this dish.

Came here as my local friends took us and the dishes are super authentic Cantonese and some touch with chao Zhou infusion. mantis shrimps, salty egg yolk fried shrimp, garlic and vermicelli noodle steam scallops were also great!

The fried pigeon was decent but not as crispy as what I’d like it to be. The clay pot rice either, just lack of that little bit to earn that wow moment. Over all highly recommend to check it out if you happen to be around temple night market.
味付けが日本人好みで、濃すぎず薄すぎず丁度よかったです。すごく美味しかったです！
うまかった！
都还是不错的，味道也蛮好的， 都还是不错的，味道也蛮好的

result.formatted_address: G/F, 184A Temple St, Jordan, 香港
result.name: 堂泰海鮮菜館

reviews.text:
Here's the worst restaurant in Hong Kong. Our dinner is ruined at here.  We waited for 40 min for a dish without any notice since our order is omitted. Even though we complained about it, they just told us to wait! I don't recommend here.

홍콩에서 겪은 최악의 식당입니다. 주문이 씹힌채로 약 40분을 기다리다 나왔습니다. 몇번을 이야기 했는데, 영어로 얘기해도 알아듣는 척... 정작 제대로 의사소통 가능한 직원은 하나 뿐이었네요. 결국 안먹고 나왔는게, 음식이 안나왔음에도 별로 미안하단 소리도 없고.. 기분 망치고 싶지 않으시면 다른데 가시는걸 추천드립니다...
値段は高めだが、活気があり良い。

새우볶음밥 돼지고기튀김볶음(?) salt and pepper 라고 써있던듯. 돼지고기 위에 뿌려진 마늘 후레이크(땅콩아님 마늘!!)가 금상첨화 ㅎ
싱겁게 먹는분께 짤수있으나
짭짤 고소함 매콤 3가지를 한번에 맛볼수있고
짜신분은 싱거운 볶음밥 냠냠 하시면 됨!
